## Common Issues

### Connection Problems
- Verify PostgreSQL is running: `pg_isready -h <host> -p <port>`
- Check network connectivity: `nc -zv <host> <port>`
- Verify credentials using `psql`

### Permission Issues
- Required permissions:
  - SELECT on system catalogs
  - USAGE on relevant schemas
  - Specific permissions for pg_stat_statements

### Performance Considerations
- Large databases may require increased work_mem
- Consider running during off-peak hours
- Use --timeout option for long-running queries

